Uses of Interface
net.xqhs.util.logging.Logger

    • Uses of Logger in net.xqhs.util.logging

      Subinterfaces of Logger in net.xqhs.util.logging 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      interface  LoggerClassic
      Any class that offers logging services to an external entity should implement this interface.
      Classes in net.xqhs.util.logging that implement Logger 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  BaseLogger
      This abstract class offers an implementation for the methods specified by the LoggerClassic interface, leaving only BaseLogger.l(net.xqhs.util.logging.Logger.Level, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object...) and BaseLogger.lr(java.lang.Object) to be implemented.
      class  DumbLogger
      This class acts as a simple implementation for the LoggerClassic interface, not connected to any of the actual Logging infrastructure.
      class  UnitComponent
      A class that extends Unit and exposes the logging and configuration methods.
      class  UnitComponentExt
      The class extends UnitComponent and also implements all methods required by the LoggerClassic interface and expose all methods as public.
